    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
      <p>This addition to the collection of the Fontaine-Maury
         Society, ca. 200 items (1 Hollinger box), ca. 1910-1920,
         1958-1991, and undated, contains correspondence, genealogies,
         photographs and a scattering of financial material. Much of it
         concerns the founding of the Fontaine Society Lending Library,
         and Lawrence Fontaine LeStourgeon is the chief correspondent.
         The photographs include Miss Maury Fontaine (ca. 1910),
         Lawrence Fontaine LeStourgeon, Matthew Fontaine Maury
         Osbourne, Philip C. Bell, Mariah G. (Fontaine) Bell, Charles
         Lee Foushee, Sr. and his family, Deborah Hobbs Fontaine,
         William Maury Fontaine, and three pictures of gravestones.</p>
    </scopecontent>
